\title{griddb: Standardized Global Grid System for Crop Simulation}
\description{
Provides tools to generate stable, globally-consistent grid cells
for use as simulation units in spatial crop modeling workflows,
along with supporting lookups for administrative/political boundaries
and crop presence masks.
}
\section{Core workflow}{

\enumerate{
\item Generate grid cells for a region with \code{\link{generate_grid_for_boundary}}
or \code{\link{generate_grid_bbox}}, then write them with
\code{\link{write_grid_to_postgis}} (or do both via
\code{\link{populate_grid_for_boundary}}).
\item Ingest administrative boundaries with \code{\link{update_admin_boundaries}}.
\item Ingest a crop presence mask with \code{\link{update_crop_mask}}.
\item Query simulation-ready cells with \code{\link{get_simulation_cells}}.
}
}

\section{Design principle}{

Cell IDs are computed from a fixed global formula
(\code{\link{compute_global_cell_id}}) rather than assigned relative
to whatever happens to be in the database. This means cells generated
for one country today retain identical IDs if the full global grid,
or another country's grid, is generated later -- there is no
renumbering or migration needed to keep results comparable across
deployments.
}

